Page 1: Introduction to Class & Object
Topic - 2 & 3: Class & Object
Class: A class is a blueprint (or) template used to create objects
. It defines the properties (data) and behaviors (methods) that the object created from it will have
.
A class is like a design or plan
.
Analogy: An architectural blueprint is used to build many houses (by the same plan); similarly, a class is used to create many objects
.
Real-World Example: Student
Data (Attributes): Name, Age, Pin number
.
(Methods) Actions: study(), attendance(), write_exam()
.
Key Insight: Instead of writing this information separately for every student, we can create a "class student" that defines properties and behaviors, then create many student objects from that class
.
