.
Page 3: Understanding Objects
Definition: An object is an instance (refers) of a class
. It is a real entity created from the class blueprint that contains actual data and can perform actions defined in the class
.
Structure vs. Reality:
A class only defines the structure
.
An object is the actual usable thing created from that structure, and memory is allocated to it
.
Real-World Example: Car
Class: Car (defines attributes like brand, colour, speed and methods like start(), stop(), accelerate())
.
Objects:
Car 1: Toyota (Brand="Toyota", Color="Red", Speed=100 k/hr)
.
Car 2: BMW
.
Page 4: Object Creation and Memory
Key Principles:
The class defines the structure, while each object holds its own data
.
Memory allocation takes place for the object itself
.
By using an object, we can call methods defined in the class
.
Object Syntax: object_name = className()
.
